 BufferedReader  :- 
 1)  It is used to read characters from any type of character input stream (String, Files, etc.)
 2) Uses Buffer internally to read characters from
 3) It is Faster
 4) Much more efficient for reading files
 5)BufferedReader can be used to read a single character at a time as well as a line at a time
 
 
     FileReader :----- 
     
 1) It can be used only for reading files
 2) Doesnâ€™t use Buffer. Directly reads from the file by accessing the hard drive.
 3) it is Slower
 4) Less efficient 
 5) It can read only one character at a time, can not read lines    